      "date": "2013-01-17 08:28:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: No score\n\nYes, I do. (I had added an inline comment indicating the bug, but being new to Gerrit, I may well have messed that up.) The comment you've added uses a C style comment marker (/*), which gets expanded by the shell to the contents of the root directory (/bin ...). Just change the marker to #, and the patch should pass the checks.",
